transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra at ScoreGlue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, my name is Terry Colvin and I placed an order for Viagra for a second time.

Speaker 1: And it's supposed to be shipped, United States Postal Service?

Speaker 2: And I was looking up the tracking number and then it says FedEx.

Speaker 1: It's going to my post office box. Can you check on that for me?

Speaker 2: Yes, I can, Mr. Colvin. Could you confirm your date of birth for me?

Speaker 1: Yes, August 29, 1952.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I do see here it's set to arrive today, and you're right.

Speaker 1: It is being shipped to your PO box.

Speaker 2: When I look up the tracking number, the reason why I'm calling you is because

Speaker 1: I had an order shipped out, I think it was on the 8th of this month,

Speaker 2: and it never got here.

Speaker 1: I called last week and I changed the delivery to, what is it, a three-day delivery?

Speaker 2: What did I change that to?

Speaker 1: Yes, so it looks like you did the two-day.

Speaker 2: Two-day. So my question, and I think there was an additional fee to that,

Speaker 1: but when I check, when I look at the tracking ID, why does it come up FedEx?

Speaker 2: So when doing FedEx, that's the only way you can do express shipping,

Speaker 1: with one-day or two-day air.

Speaker 2: Will it go to my post office box, though?

Speaker 1: It should, or usually the post office will hold it if it's not in your PO box.

Speaker 2: Okay, so they didn't give me, I sent my wife,

Speaker 1: I was expecting bills and we have a post office box in Bozeman,

Speaker 2: and she said it wasn't in the post office box.

Speaker 1: Should I have her stand in line and check on it?

Speaker 2: Well, looking here, it looks like it's going to be delivered before 5 p.m. Bozeman time.

Speaker 1: So that does give it, I'd say, like an hour or so, right?

Speaker 2: So it should be there by the end of the day.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'm only asking because it came up FedEx and I'm not knowledgeable about it.

Speaker 2: And so I really, I wanted it registered so I'd have to sign for it,

Speaker 1: but that's not the case.

Speaker 2: You couldn't offer that to a PO box, is that correct?

Speaker 1: No, sir, because it would just be dropped off at the PO box because you're not always there.

Speaker 2: Sometimes what happens is they do drop it off with the representative who is working.

Speaker 1: So say it's at a post office with a PO box, they'll drop it off at the post office,

Speaker 2: and then you have to sign for it with them.

Speaker 1: Okay, but there was no notification.

Speaker 2: But you answered my question, so I guess it is going to my post office box,

Speaker 1: and FedEx is the only way I can get two-day air, and it should show up sometime today, is that correct?

Speaker 2: Exactly correct.

Speaker 1: I have no idea why my last order that I ordered on the 8th of the month,

Speaker 2: well, actually it was on the 6th, it was supposed to be shipped, I never got it.

Speaker 1: I'm wondering if it was stolen.

Speaker 2: Interesting.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and I've had problems like that before.

Speaker 2: Well, I thank you for your time.

Speaker 1: Yeah, of course.

Speaker 2: And I appreciate it. Thank you, bud.

Speaker 1: Yep, thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye bye.
